There is a an issue with CCLabelTextFormatter::MultilineText, in some cases it starts new line with an empty line. It happens when we use break line with space under conditions:

nonCJKWord.empty() == true
lineIsEmpty == true
last_word.empty() == true
character == ' ' // space 0x20

My suggestion is to add this condition branch to the `if (!nonCJKword.empty())` condition:

```
else if (StringUtils::isUnicodeSpace(character) && lineIsEmpty && last_word.empty())
{
    continue;
}
```

Hi ,

The HttpClient for iOS always set a content-type (in the http headers) to "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" for PUT request.
I think that's an issue because all put requests are not limited to this content type!

For example i need to use "application/json" to be compliant with my REST webservices...

The android version of HttpClient is not affected.

Issue can be fixed by removing the following lines from HttpClient-apple.mm:

```
if ([requestType isEqual: @"PUT"])
{
    [nsrequest setValue: @"application/x-www-form-urlencoded" forHTTPHeaderField: @"Content-Type"];
}
```

Thank you!

